    </div>

  
    <h4>Biography</h4>
    <div class='note'>
      <p>Jeremy Kerr works for Canonical, as a Linux kernel developer, on the hardware enablement team.</p>
<p>Jeremy has contributed to a range of other Open Source projects as well, such as petitboot (a <span class="caps">GUI</span> bootloader), K42 (a research operating system), patchwork (a web-based patch-tracking system) and nfsim (the netfilter simulation environment).</p>
<p>Jeremy&#8217;s interests lie in operating system kernels, Linux on <span class="caps">ARM</span>, and the Cell/B.E. &amp; PowerPC architectures.</p>
    </div>
  
  
  
  
  
      
